Solution: WhoaMan needs to <a href="http://copyright.gov/onlinesp/" class="postlink">register</a> with the US Copyright Office as the designated agent of a service provider under OCILLA. This must be done through a mailed paper form and requires the payment of a fee, currently $105 for the designation plus $35 for up to 10 domains.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Oct 17, 2014 5:49 pm</p><hr />
