<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11928&amp;p=135186#p135186"><![CDATA[
Well, there are other forums (like NA) where ROM posting isn't prohibited, so the benefits of such prohibition are not clear cut. I think if ROM posting is allowed, it should be for cases where it's clearly beneficial to the community in some way, not just dumping the entire NES library on the forum just because the rules allow it.<br /><br />It'd be best if we could have a public discussion about the forum rules and actually publish them somewhere. The server administrator can take part in the conversation, and can choose to accept whatever rules the community comes up with or veto them.<br /><br />It'd be good if we could come up with an actual policy, though, rather than referencing the late Parodius network rules.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Fri Oct 17, 2014 1:08 pm</p><hr />
